selectedmemories.Title: Last Year's Man
selectedmemories.description: I listened to this song often on the journey to high school during an unseasonably warm September. That summer I had just discovered Leonard Cohen's music and was enchanted.  I shared the albums I obsessed over during the holiday with someone I started dating when the school term began. I remember once after school we sat in a park atop a big hill and listened to this song on wired headphones we split, nestled under  our jackets we'd prop up over some sticks for shade.

selectedmemories.Title: Money, Money, Money
selectedmemories.description: Moving to England from Sri Lanka with my family. My uncle picking us up at the airport and driving us to his family’s home. My cousin asking me if I know what a television is. Me replying I don’t know. Seeing a television set for the first time.

selectedmemories.Title: Roslyn
selectedmemories.description: I was sitting in my friend Abby's car, late at night, right before she was about to drive me home for the evening. We had spent the night playing billiards in her parent's house and being in a hot-tub under the stars, and I was probably a bit or a lot in love. The song came on and we sat there in her driveway looking at the sky, in that kind of quiet that exists only that late at night as you can feel there is a sense of an ending.

selectedmemories.Title: Baby Beluga
selectedmemories.description: Sitting in the back of my mom’s green Volkswagen station wagon as she drives me and my best friend to dance class, my mom is singing along to the music

selectedmemories.Title: You've Got a Friend
selectedmemories.description: This was a song that I frequently listened to during a difficult time in my childhood.  My father had died and my mother was terminally ill. I would listen to the song in our living room which was the only room that had a stereo. I would be alone. I would play the entire album repeatedly which had a number of songs that I identified with and that provided comfort to me. The songs helped me understand what I was going through and gave me hope.
selectedmemories.emoextra: despair, contentedness, affirming, empathy, hopeful, optimism

selectedmemories.Title: Pink + White
selectedmemories.description: This memory occurred on a trip to Sri Lanka. After traveling from the US to Sri Lanka I had just got into a van hired to take us to our hotel. My family, including my Dad, Mom, and Sister were there. As we drove from the airport to our hotel I played the album Blonde and remember listening to Pink + White while looking at the palm trees outside the car.

selectedmemories.Title: Izzo (H.O.V.A)
selectedmemories.description: It was in 2001 and I was on the train to somewhere with my big brother after having weeks earlier emigrated to the UK. My big bro who had lived in the UK for a couple years prior put his over ear headphones on my ears and told me to "listen to this". This was the first hip hop song I had ever heard and I loved. It spawned a deep love and affinity to this music and suffice to say was quite a formative moment.

selectedmemories.Title: Wake me up before you go go
selectedmemories.description: Reminds me of my younger days, in school, and listening to the song - dancing, singing, and overall having not stress and enjoying life.

selectedmemories.Title: Moondance
selectedmemories.description: In college I was in an a cappella singing group and this song was my solo my freshman year. I have fond memories of singing it with my friends and group mates in our rehearsal room, college chapel, brick steps under the bridge to our art museum on campus, at other college performance halls and on stage.

selectedmemories.Title: Terrible Love
selectedmemories.description: This song was playing in the car when my brother and best friend were dropping me off at the Seattle-Tacoma airport for me to fly to Geneva, Switzerland for a 4 month study abroad. It was a cloudy morning with a little bit of misting rain. I was sitting in the front passenger seat. I had just broken up with my boyfriend two days prior, and I recall missing him, being very sad to leave all my friends, and fairly anxious/nervous about the logistics of my travel and the upcoming semester.

selectedmemories.Title: Pump It Up
selectedmemories.description: At boarding school, on days with heavy snow we were expected to get up early and shovel snow around campus before going to classes. I would blast this song to wake people up. My room was on the third floor, I can remember the physical environment: hallways and stairwell, doors, etc. but less so who was in each room. Memory happened over several years, so maybe that is why only the consistent environmental elements are there

selectedmemories.Title: Iris
selectedmemories.description: Iris by the Goo Goo Dolls reminds me of early adolescent summer camp dances. Each dance had three slow dances and Iris was one of the tracks selected. The song reminds me of the carefree years of middle school where I my biggest concern was whether I would slow dance with my crush (I did).

selectedmemories.Title: Vellai Pura ondru
selectedmemories.Artist: Artist: K. J. Yesudas Movie: Pudhu Kavithai (Tamil)
selectedmemories.description: This was a song my dad used to play in our first home.

selectedmemories.Title: Running up that hill
selectedmemories.description: I was in the backseat of a car with 3 friends and my boyfriend. We were on holiday in France and driving through the countryside to a bakery. My friend turned on the radio and this song was playing, I remember looking at the surrounding area and fields and feeling content.

selectedmemories.Title: You Send Me
selectedmemories.description: It reminds me of a time in my life a few years ago with an ex partner, I sort of remember it being at their house but I guess it's an overall feeling, we used to sing it a lot together, and a specific memory of walking home late at night under building works singing it together and felt a lot of love for each other.
selectedmemories.emoextra: love, appreciation, serenity, mutual affection, empathy, trust, understanding

selectedmemories.Title: Summer Nights
selectedmemories.description: It is a summer's day and I am leaving my house alone to walk to school. I am singing this song to myself and I remember it being the first time that year I can leave the house without a jacket. I relish the warmth and novelty of a warm summer's day in England. I don't believe the memory is because of the song's title - just that it was a very popular song at the time.

selectedmemories.Title: Ash Grove
selectedmemories.description: This song was sung regularly at the summer camp for girls I attended in my teen years. It was often sung in the closing circle ceremony at the end of the day and was sung in beautiful harmony by the 100 or so girl campers.

selectedmemories.Title: it's all coming back to me now
selectedmemories.description: I remember my mum playing this in the car in summer. I remember she was a Celine Dion fan so this was one of the tapes which got played a lot as I rode around with her my brother and sister.

selectedmemories.Title: Jika Sempat
selectedmemories.description: I remember the song specifically with the memory of being in a music studio and with a band of my friends practicing the song for an upcoming performance for an event by a society in university. I was sitting at the side, listening in and giving feedback as I was the director. I remember feeling emotional trying to envision how great the song would be on stage, and because it was on valentines, I was also overwhelmed with emotion as I was developing feelings for a friend in the band.

selectedmemories.Title: Closing Time
selectedmemories.description: I was at a dance on the last night of a summer reading camp that I attended during high school.  I was with the whole camp, specifically dancing with other girls in my "pod".  The camp was at Amherst College.  It was one of the happiest times of my life and this was the last song on the last night, so when I left the next day I listened to the song on repeat and cried.

selectedmemories.Title: Starships
selectedmemories.description: A youth group sleepover with one of my best friends at the time (and other youth) in a church we hadn't visited before. All full of sugar from sweeties and wanted a jump around and be loud so we put on Nicki Minaj Starships while in our jammies and sleeping bags and had a proper wee boogie.

selectedmemories.Title: Use Somebody
selectedmemories.description: First year university, near the end of the year- dancing at a club (downstairs on the corner) in Gastown with the European group from 4th floor. I was with Pat and Toby, we all started singing together in a circle when this song came on.

selectedmemories.Title: Just The Girl
selectedmemories.description: I remember being in the car with my mother, sister and uncle when this song played on the radio. I was really enjoying this song when my mother asked my uncle to turn it off.

selectedmemories.Title: Miss you
selectedmemories.description: I was driving home from my best friend‘s house of that time. We used to spend a lot of time together, nearly dated, were very close. This song reminds me of the foggy autumn evenings of my home in Austria, the tranquility of driving in the dark and of the numerous wonderful days spent with my friend.

selectedmemories.Title: Pulse width
selectedmemories.description: Was spring first year of univeristy, smoking cigarettes with a close friend watching the sun rise as we pulled an all-nighter for exam revision. We set up some kitchen chairs outside and listened to the track through some speakers.

selectedmemories.Title: Come Healing
selectedmemories.description: I first heard the song while watching the movie "The Farewell," and was quite struck by it. I'd just gone through a breakup. About a week later, the world shut down due to Covid. The song stuck with me, so much so that soon after, I began to teach it to myself on guitar and played it every night for a year while living at home with my parents and dog again. I still play it, though with not as much frequency, at it brings back both happy and sad memories.

selectedmemories.Title: Take a chance on me
selectedmemories.description: I was at a JLS concert and one of the band members sat on the edge of the stage and sang this song to a couple of us. I was around 14 and with one of my friends at the concert.

selectedmemories.Title: Paranoid Android
selectedmemories.description: Visiting my girlfriend at university for the weekend. We were sitting in her bedroom and playing each other music that we liked. I played Radiohead, it was the first time she had heard the band and she really liked their passion.

selectedmemories.Title: January
selectedmemories.description: Secondary School discos in 1977 ~ cold and dark. Very dodgy outfits and lots of dancing in circles around handbags. Nervous anticipation about being asked to dance or worse still not!

selectedmemories.Title: Yellow
selectedmemories.description: It was 2000, and the Leonid meteor shower was passing over the UK - my two friends came over for a sleepover and we lay on the lawn outside most of the night watching the shooting stars. We were all heavily into the Parachutes album at that point and were singing 'Yellow'. It was a really lovely, otherworldly, comradely night, I remember it being cold and damp and dewy on the grass but not minding at all. We had probably had a couple of drinks! The song always reminds me of that night.

selectedmemories.Title: Strawberry Swing
selectedmemories.description: I was with my first boyfriend. We didn't have much in common- but his favourite song was Strawberry Swing. I used to listen to it to calm me down when I missed him, normally before bed. It was a caring song that comforted me a lot. It still brings me a lot of peace now, even after our relationship went sour.

selectedmemories.Title: Ride of the Valkyries
selectedmemories.description: I was in my childhood home, watching my little brother race around the table as soon as we put the song on.  I was with my parents.

selectedmemories.Title: Bicycle Race
selectedmemories.description: It always reminds me of visiting my grandparents. My parents always used to play Queens Greatest Hits in the car on the way there, and it was the song that I most looked forward to hearing.

selectedmemories.Title: loosing my religion
selectedmemories.description: I remember going to family functions and the band would play this song all the time

selectedmemories.Title: You make me feel so young
selectedmemories.description: We had frank sinatra - you make me feel so young for our first dance at our wedding. My husband and I were dancing in the middle of the dance floor surrounded by people we loved, celebrating our wedding.

selectedmemories.Title: Rocket Man
selectedmemories.description: I was at an outdoor music event with my friends, dancing in the darkness.

selectedmemories.Title: Don't Wanna Miss a Thing
selectedmemories.description: This song was used for the first dance at my wedding.  It takes me straight back to dancing with my new wife with all our friends and family around us.

selectedmemories.Title: A Thousand Years
selectedmemories.description: I was at home and I was holding my cat, Isabelle. I started singing this song to her. I could see that it was relaxing her. She started purring and then fell asleep.

selectedmemories.Title: Lost On You
selectedmemories.description: First time when i hear this song i was in italy in venice with my partner and i hear it so many times when i waalking on the streets in different cities from italy, so always when i hear this song it remind me about this happy times i had there in italy.

selectedmemories.Title: I'm just a kid
selectedmemories.description: I remember hanging out at a friends house getting ready to throw a party. It was a summer afternoon and we were going to have a lot of people over at their house. We all started singing this song and it really got us in the mood for the party. Every time I hear this song it reminds me of that day, because it brings me back to a time when I did not have a care in the world. It makes me feel like I had nothing to worry about and just got to enjoy life.

selectedmemories.Title: Born in the USA
selectedmemories.description: Being in a cafe in Donegal, with my future wife. It was a sunny day, and the cafe were playing this, it was the summer (probably August) of 1985, the town was possibly Glencolmcille

selectedmemories.Title: Ticket to ride
selectedmemories.description:
I remember being really young when i first heard this song. Maybe i was 8 or 9 years old and i remember playing with my brother and then hearing this song on my mothers radio coming from the kitchen.

I loved the song straight away and me and my brother were dancing that day.

selectedmemories.Title: fake plastic trees
selectedmemories.description: I feel i listened to this song when i had stress and mayhem in my life and just wanted peace and i was on my own and sitting by myself. i think the song is very melodic and soothing and i thought things can not be so bad and if i can feel calm in that moment just from listening to a song, then i can apply this to my life as i think life does not have to be full of stress there is good and everything is not always bad and i have to be mindful and think in the moment.

selectedmemories.Title: Love will keep us together
selectedmemories.description: Was a really young kid, like 3 years old, and driving with my mom to the store in Laguna beach.  The windows were down and the weather was nice.   We got to the store and everything was in clear plexiglass display cases.  She bought me a toy.  I remember there being lots of eucalyptus which smelled really nice.   After we shopped I got my hair cut at Rudy’s barber shop and was afraid he was goi g to accidentally cut my ear again as he had done before.   It was a great day with my mom out on the

selectedmemories.Title: Making your mind up
selectedmemories.description: It takes me back to being about 4 years old and singing it in front of my family. I remeber everyone clapping and cheering as I was giving my best dance moves. It's always been referred to as my song ever since.

selectedmemories.Title: Touch me in the morning
selectedmemories.description: This song reminds me of when I said goodbye to someone I loved. He was leaving to live in another country and myself and a group of friends went to say goodbye as he was leaving. This happened at university.

selectedmemories.Title: ALMOST PARADISE
selectedmemories.description: It was my first dance   The CYO dance was the first I was permitted to attend

selectedmemories.Title: I want to know what love is
selectedmemories.description: It was cold outside and I was walking my dog. I was 15 years old. I had just bought a Sony Walkman and I was listening to the song. I realized how cool music can be and I enjoyed the audio quality of the new Walkman. I just remember being immersed in the song and realizing the profound impact music and songs can have.

selectedmemories.Title: Breaking the habit
selectedmemories.description: Being at home at my parents house. After school talking to friends online. Playing video games and listening to music at the same time. Using myspace as social media. Lounging on a bean bag.

selectedmemories.Title: Sugar We're Going Down
selectedmemories.description: II remember hanging out with a friend named Katie. We were walking around the mall and just so happened to bump into Cody. We were just store hopping not actually shopping. We walk into this one store called Spensers. The song just comes on and Cody starts to jam out. I just remember hearing the drums right away and my ears perk out, I was so invested with the song that it is my go to song.

selectedmemories.Title: yesterday once more
selectedmemories.description: I was in the car with my parents and brother. I can't remember where we are going but I remember my mum was singing. It was a happy moment

selectedmemories.Title: Pretty (Ugly Before)
selectedmemories.description: I was laying in bed during summer and talking to someone at the time who I ended up becoming romantically involved with. I just remember this song washing over me and giving me a strong sense of confidence.

selectedmemories.Title: I'm still standing
selectedmemories.description: It was christmas day.  Myself ans my two sisters had bought the album for my Dad for Christmas.  Were were playing on a new computer set up right in the middle of the living room and this album was on and this is the song we all knew and sang and danced and were happy to.

selectedmemories.Title: Tondo
selectedmemories.description: This is a song that reminds me of when I went to go and see Folamour perform live. It was my favourite song out of the whole set and took me a long time to track down the name of the song and find it online.

selectedmemories.Title: final countdown
selectedmemories.description: ?This song always brings back memories of my childhood, it was the first real song I like and always remember it being played in the kitchen of my family home.

selectedmemories.Title: Triumph
selectedmemories.description:
J Hus - Triumph is a song from the album 'Big Conspiracy'. This album came out during lockdown in 2020 and I listened to the whole album daily while I was working. Triumph for some reason is the song which reminds me most about that time even though it's not my favourite song on the album.

It reminds me of a time when a lot of things were going on in the world, however it evokes positive emotions from a simpler time.

selectedmemories.Title: Fix you
selectedmemories.description: I went to my first ever gig which was Coldplay and I drove from my home town to Bolton to get there. It took several hours and I went with my then girlfriend. I was a big coldplay fan and it was the biggest car journey I'd done myself since passing my test too. I remember that fix you was the last song and it was used in the music video too, which went on to be a massive hit.

selectedmemories.Title: Music Sounds Better WIth You
selectedmemories.description: This song came out in 1998, and it reminds me of playing football outside on a sunny day during the summer with my friends.

selectedmemories.Title: superheroes
selectedmemories.description: i was listening to this song a lot during a specific time period in college and whilst listening to this specific song i had found out from a group that my business teacher (who was my favourite) had suddenly died which was a huge shock. whenever i hear the song, i instantly think of that scene and the teacher.

selectedmemories.Title: Follow Me
selectedmemories.description: My first time in Ibiza, sorrounded by my closest friends. It reminds me of a time where I was care free, enjoying life and having fun and laughs with my friends before we had children and responsibilities, it makes me feel happy and proud of living my life to the fullest.

selectedmemories.Title: dark side of the moon
selectedmemories.description: this was 1 of the all time great albums.it was at a time when i was influenced by music.the whole of the album runs with no breaks,which was unique

selectedmemories.Title: Children
selectedmemories.description: The memory that I associate with this is being on holiday at the pool. It was the first time I had heard this song and it made me instantly feel like I was in a dream. The song really connected with me and made me feel relaxed and happy. Whilst the song played we were jumping in the pool and having a really good time. I didn't initially know what the song was til a later date.

selectedmemories.Title: Unfinished Sympathy
selectedmemories.description: My favourite song in university. I overplayed it considerably and eventually sort of forgot about it. Years later, I moved by myself to another country, it was a lonely experience and I struggled a few weeks. One Friday evening, I went out to a bar and was pondering if I should move back home again when the song started playing, the happy memories flooded in, I ended up talking to a group of other expats who were also in the bar and we became friends, I stayed in the country for year

selectedmemories.Title: January February
selectedmemories.description: This song reminds me of being a very small child and being very close with my mother at home. It brings feelings of happiness, innocence and security whenever I hear it.

selectedmemories.Title: Ruiner
selectedmemories.description: This song reminds me of a previous breakup In went through. It reminds me of a girlfriend I had for almost two years who I mutually broke up with because we no longer saws things the same. It was a major letdown for me as I truly loved her and I am convinced she felt the same. I listened to this song a lot throughout this time and it without fail reminds me of the hurt I felt.

selectedmemories.Title: Love Song
selectedmemories.description: This song reminds me of the boy I loved. However, we met at the wrong time in our lives and we couldn't be together. Every time I hear this song, I remember when we were sitting on a park bench and looking at each other, knowing that tomorrow we had to part and that it would be the biggest mistake of our lives. And it was a mistake, but there was no other way.

selectedmemories.Title: Count to Six and Die (The Vacuum of Infinite Space Encompassing)
selectedmemories.description: I listened to this particular track on repeat when I realized my first marriage was all but over. It was a sheer realization after a particularly nasty argument with him at our little apartment where we lived; it felt like something breaking inside me. I seriously considered killing myself: was in a foreign country, I had absolutely nothing, and I'd be going back to my homeland to more nothing since my own family didn't want me back. It was the end of the dream I had fought so hard for.

selectedmemories.Title: Mr Brightside
selectedmemories.description: This was one of my favorite songs when I was growing up. I went to see the band at a gig in 2007 in London, with my two best friends.

selectedmemories.Title: walk like an egyptian
selectedmemories.description: Walk like an Egyptian was a top song of 1987 i think. This was played all the time on the radio when I was a young kid and i can remember this song being played on the TV show Top of the Pops. In the music video the people made the classic egyptian walk movement. I can remember having a birthday party and this song was played and me, my friends and family did the walk like an egyptian walk. I can still remember it now and it often reminds me of that time when i hear that song now. A great song.

selectedmemories.Title: Tonight I'm loving you
selectedmemories.description: I used to listen to this song while driving to school and work. I would listen to it anywhere I went like shopping etc, mostly with my sisters. It was such a carefree time of my life, just having fun, driving fast listening to this song.

selectedmemories.Title: Wish you were here
selectedmemories.description: Following completion of 6th form at school, me and my friend went on a 2 week tour of Western European countries by car. I distinctly recall this song being played on the car cassette when we were traversing through the Alps. For me this song perfectly encapsulated the environment that we were in and always brings this memory whenever I hear the song anywhere such as YouTube.

selectedmemories.Title: Cornerstone
selectedmemories.description: This song evokes thanksgiving and joy in me whenever I listen to it since my 40th birthday. It brings back memories of childhood looking forward to become an adult.

selectedmemories.Title: Shine
selectedmemories.description: My husband had left me and my two children, 1 and 4 year olds. I had no job, the house to pay for and the children to bring up.  He left for another woman and he didn't pay towards his children or see them regularly.  This was my song that gave me hope for the future.  I am now very happily married to the love of my life and my children have grown into successful adults.

selectedmemories.Title: What's New Pussycat
selectedmemories.description: I used to sing "What's New Pussycat" to one of my cats. She fell ill and the surgery intended to save her ended up doing more harm than good. I sang it to her again at the veterinary hospital, before she was euthanized. Whenever I hear the words or tune I think of her.

selectedmemories.Title: Hey Jude
selectedmemories.description: I was 14 years old and I was waiting to hear the first playing of the new single by my favourite group…The Beatles.I knew it was going to be played on the BBC radio at 1o’clock and so as it was a sunny day I tied my portable radio to the front of my pushbike and went for a ride alone on a track across the South Downs overlooking Brighton where I lived.I can still picture my self being amazed by the song and by the end I stopped riding my bike and had to just sit and listen to it….it was amazing.

selectedmemories.Title: Coffee
selectedmemories.description: I see freshman year in Chapel Hill - HoJo specifically. I don't have many friends and I don't like my roommate, but I randomly bump into a group of people one night on my way to the louge who immediately become my best friends. They love my laugh, they love my Adventure Time shirt, they love me. After class, we'd all hang in Luke and Ahmed's room and listen to Sylvan Esso's debut album on repeat and eat tons of dining hall cookies.

selectedmemories.Title: Close to You
selectedmemories.description: I was still at school and dating a boy from the same school. I was becoming very fond of him and I was at home with my parents one day when I heard this song on the radio. I knew then that I wanted to be close to him always. We’ve been married for 48 years.

selectedmemories.Title: smoke on the water
selectedmemories.description: it was one of the first gigs i ever attended and my favourite songs. I was with my best mate. It brings back strong memories of indpendence and youth and enjoyment

selectedmemories.Title: Bang a Gong
selectedmemories.description: This song was around the year I was 14 or 15 and during the summer I had a lot of freedom and remember hearing this song all the time. My friends loved it too and we used to sing it together. We used to meet at a weir pool and play T Rex music and go swimming. Later in the summer I had a bad stomach bug due to swimming in the dirty water and was confined to bed but still listened to this music.

selectedmemories.Title: Oops upside your head
selectedmemories.description:
My best friend and I had a joint 21st birthday party at a local nightclub. It was late 1980's and we went to the club every weekend. The outside of it was where they filmed the outside of Fawlty Towers, so it was called Fawlty's. We had a great night & loads of family & friends came. 
Oops Upside your head came on and everyone got onto the floor and sat in rows behind each other and did the usual dance to the song with each of us at the head of a line

selectedmemories.Title: Liar
selectedmemories.description: I was watching The old Grey Whistle test on BBC at home late at night. My mother was in bed I just fell in love with the singer I was probably about 15 then. Mesmerising I couldn't take my eyes off him and that's probably how my love for music started. No one had heard of the band then, my school friends hadn't or record shop where I went to order LP Queen

selectedmemories.Title: The little Drummer Boy
selectedmemories.description: The lead up to Christmas as a child. The excitement, the love, and feeling safe.

selectedmemories.Title: sweet child of mine
selectedmemories.description: I was with one of my closest friend.We were on a short break by the seaside and we were stayng in an hotel that had MTV. it was a good break.

selectedmemories.Title: Sealed with a kiss
selectedmemories.description: It was in the 70s. I was holidaying with my friend Sandra and her family. We were camping in a large family tent on a campsite called Reighton Sands. It was a very hot summer, we were in our teens so we could wander around the campsite freely. We would go in the clubhouse a lot, the kids clubroom had a dukebox, they had this record in it (sealed with a kiss) and I would play it every time.

selectedmemories.Title: Yesterday once More
selectedmemories.description: I was about 10 years odl, it was summer we would take a radio to our local park with my friends and would all sing along when we heard this song, there was a young gilr from London visiting her grandmother for the summer, when I hear this song I remeber her

selectedmemories.Title: The first time ever I saw your face
selectedmemories.description: It was the music for the first dance at my wedding. It evokes wonderful memories of my wedding day, the smile that never left my husband's face, the joy of the occasion and having all my friends and family around me - some of who are no longer with us,

selectedmemories.Title: Where do broken hearts go
selectedmemories.description: My mum and dad both loved listening to my neice singing this when she was young. Sadly they both died to soon and my neice recorded the song which was played at both of their funerals. Now when I hear this song played it upsets me so much even though it has good memories of Happy times it also gives me great sadness too.

selectedmemories.Title: We are the Champions
selectedmemories.description: I was in a dead end job and hadn't even realised I was being bullied by my boss ever day. I saw a much more interesting job advertised, applied and got it.  I sang this song in my head relentlessy after I got the phone call.

selectedmemories.Title: Edelwiss
selectedmemories.description:
I listened to this song with my mom whilst she was terminally ill with cancer. Due to my mom being of a European background this music was soothing to her and bought back nice memories of her childhood, although this was a sad song.
This also was the song in the Sound of Music, a musical which we both liked. 
Whenever I hear this song I will always think of my mom. A song which we both shared and liked for different reasons.

selectedmemories.Title: puppet on a string
selectedmemories.description: I remember playing this song frequently around my sixth birthday and insiting it was used for all the musical games such as musical statues, musical bumps and pass the parcel at my sixth birthday party. I had my school friends at the party which took place at the family home.

selectedmemories.Title: Suburbia
selectedmemories.description: It's more a general memory of when I was at VIth form College. We we all just old enough to be served i pubs without being challenged and this was a song that seemed to be constantly played in one of the pubs near College  Pub quiz machines were becoming popular and because my group of friends were studying a variety of subjects and had a variety of interests we used to regularly win large amounts of money.  The song seems to go with the sound of £1 coins hitting the tray

selectedmemories.Title: Every little thing she does is magic
selectedmemories.description: It was at my sisters birthday party and i was responsible for putting on the music. I put this on because it is a good song and i reminded me of one of the friends of my sister which i liked and she was at the party and she was dancing.

selectedmemories.Title: HIGH
selectedmemories.description: IT WAS A SONG ME AND MY THEN PARTNER AT THE TIME CHOOSE AS OUR FUTURE WEDING SONG, IT BRINGS BACK MANY MEMORIES OF BEING MARRIED YOUNG, THE ANNVERSARYS OF LISTENING TO THE SONG AND STIL WHEN I HEAR IT 26 YEARS ATER IT TAKES ME BACK TO THAT TIME WHEN I WA MARRIED AND THE THINGS WE DID WHILST MARRIED.

selectedmemories.Title: Love Don't Live Here Anymore
selectedmemories.description: I remember as a girl this song being on the radio whilst I had breakfast.  I was on a breakfast stool sitting at the bar in the kitchen eating Ready Brek.  I don't like Ready Brek so I recall this song and the dislike of the cereal at the same time!  This would be in the mid to late 70's in my childhood home.

selectedmemories.Title: Hey Jude
selectedmemories.description: I was fairly young and listening to this record, with my sisters, at my parents house. We were sitting in our front room where the record player was and my eldest sister put this record on.  At first, I didn't particularly like it but after my sister played it a few times, I found it quite haunting and started to come round to it.  I had previously thought that I had bought the record but on reflection, I think my sister did.

selectedmemories.Title: Something's Got A Hold Of My Heart
selectedmemories.description:
In my bedroom alone; sitting at my dressing table getting ready to go out that night. It was a Saturday and I was meeting my boyfriend in the city. I'd bought this record earlier that day and played it over and over on my portable record player that mum and dad had bought me for my birthday.
I think the repeated playing of it drove my parents mad, but they didn't say anything.

selectedmemories.Title: ONE LOVE
selectedmemories.description: IN OUR HOUSEHOLD THE SONG WAS PLAYED A LOT AND WHEN BOB MARLEY DIED, THAT SONG WAS PLAYED A LOT ON THE RADIO OVER A LONG PERIOD OF TIME. JAMAICANS LOVE THAT SONG AND SING IT A LOT AT PARTIES.

selectedmemories.Title: Bohemian Rhapsody
selectedmemories.description: This song was a Number 1 hit on the pop charts in the UK for what seemed like weeks, if I recall correctly. It reminds me of being in high school/secondary school. My friends and I liked the song. At the end of the school term, classes were a bit more relaxed; we had P.E in the gym but the teacher left the class alone playing ball games. It was very loud with everyone shouting and laughing, and my best friend and I sat at the side and for some reason started singing Bohemian Rhapsody out loud.
selectedmemories.emoextra: Friendship and bonding, sharing something that made us both laugh because of the unusual lyrics in the song.

selectedmemories.Title: i'm not in love
selectedmemories.description: It was in the charts the year I met my husband, it was 1975 and life was good. Dave was my first proper boyfriend and I thought he was fab and so good looking and he was my new boyfriend, We went   local pub in the side room where all the younger people hung out to the local pub this  record was playing on the jukebox, This track always takes me back to that year and how happy I was. We are no longer together and there are things I regret and this song always reminds me of Dave .

selectedmemories.Title: Ghost Town
selectedmemories.description: I remember the UK events in 1981. Widespread unemployment, inner city riots and just a general feeling of despondency amongst the adults. I was still a child and living with my parents at home in Salford.

selectedmemories.Title: Return To Sender
selectedmemories.description: This is the first record I bought with my own money.  I also bought it on the way to see a friend which involved taking a bus to a strange town for the first time alone.  I was 13/14 and felt very grown up although I'm sure I wasn't.  This was also unusual as I was never a big Elvis fan, more if a Beatles girl.  When I hear this song it takes me back immediately

selectedmemories.Title: We Are The Champions
selectedmemories.description: The song reminds me of several things that all took place in the year the song was released. On that year, I moved to a different area for the first time in my life, the car factory in the town I was leaving closed, and a bird sanctuary in the place I was moving to opened. I also recall that the weather that winter was particularly harsh, mostly due to frost.

selectedmemories.Title: Row your boat
selectedmemories.description: This is a song that I used to sing to my children, along with actions, when they were toddlers. Sung at home and it usually resulted in us all falling about with laughter.

selectedmemories.Title: FIELDS OF FIRE
selectedmemories.description: My friend and I were 13 and it was the first song that we heard on the radio that made us go "Wow!".  We begged our parents to let us see the play live in Glasgow and it was the first live music conceet we attended.  The sight of the crowd bouncing to the music, the incredible noise from the band, the feeling of the music literally resonating within your body is still a visceral and almost tangible memory.  It defined my love of live music and every cooncert I remember this
